# AI-SDLC + Cursor Runtime

This repository uses **Cursor** as the agent runtime for AI-SDLC pipelines.

## Runtime contract

- Orchestrator invokes `cursor-agent --print --force --output-format=stream-json`
- Auth: `CURSOR_API_KEY` (required for pipeline runs)
- Optional model override: `AI_SDLC_CURSOR_MODEL`
- MCP advisor: `.cursor/mcp.json` → `@ai-sdlc/mcp-advisor`

## Configuration sources

| Concern | Path |
| --- | --- |
| Pipeline | `.ai-sdlc/pipeline.yaml` |
| Agent role | `.ai-sdlc/agent-role.yaml` |
| Quality gates | `.ai-sdlc/quality-gate.yaml` |
| Autonomy | `.ai-sdlc/autonomy-policy.yaml` |

## Commands

```sh
npm run ai-sdlc:check-cursor   # verify Cursor runtime
npm run ai-sdlc:health         # validate AI-SDLC config
npm run ai-sdlc:run -- --issue 42
```

## Invariants

- Do not edit `.github/workflows/**` or `.ai-sdlc/**` during agent code stages unless the task explicitly requires it.
- Run `npm run build` before claiming a change is complete.
- Prefer Tailwind utilities over raw CSS (except `src/styles/global.css` if added later).
